  let x = 10;
  const y = 20;
  console.log(x, y); // âœ… Works inside
}
console.log(x, y);   // âŒ Error â€” not visible outside


âœ… They are block-scoped â€” only visible inside { }.

ğŸŸ¨ 2. var â†’ Function Scope (or Global if outside a function)

If you use var, it does not care about { } (blocks).
It only cares about functions or the global area.

Example:

