  var z = 30;
}
console.log(z);  // âœ… Works â€” z is visible outside the block!


â—Even though z was declared inside the if,
because it used var, it becomes global (visible everywhere in the file).

ğŸ§© Function Scope Example

If var is declared inside a function, itâ€™s only visible inside that function.

